      "content": "Originalism is the legal doctrine that insists the Constitution must be interpreted according to the original public meaning of its text at the time it was ratified. The core justification is that the Constitution is a fixed document, not a living thing that judges can rewrite based on modern preferences. Therefore, judges must adhere to the framers' intent to maintain the rule of law and prevent judicial overreach into policy-making.",
